ij denotes the effect of developmental stage j within locality i and t
ik is the effect of temperature k within locality i. Index i ranges over values CAT (Catarpe) and TAT (El Tatio), while j is either 36 or 42 and k is either 20 or 25. With appropriate constraints on the model coefficients, this model allows the effect of temperature at each locality to be assessed while controlling any effect due to developmental stage.
